[
  "Pawan Munjal, son of late Brijmohan Lall Munjal, founder of Hero Group, who died in 2015 at age 92, runs motorcycle flagship Hero MotoCorp. ",
  "A former partner of Japan's Honda, Hero is the world's largest producer of two-wheelers by volume having sold over 95 million units to date.",
  "After parting ways with Honda in 2011, Pawan has led a global expansion with factories in Colombia and Bangladesh. ",
  "Hero has a research unit in Jaipur city that employs 700 engineers and a tech center in Germany. ",
  "After plummeting during the pandemic lockdown, an uptick in rural demand led to sales of two-wheelers returning to close to pre-pandemic levels in July 2020.  "
]